The inaugural Bidco Classic golf tournament hosted by Bidco Africa was held at Sigona Golf Club on May 6. Sigona golfer Nitin Shah emerged the winner. Playing off handicap 7, Shah posted an impressive 41 points on the par 72 Sigona Golf Club, getting 21 points on the first nine and 20 points on the back nine. Present were Bidco group CEO Thiagarajan Ramamurthy and Sigona Golf Club chairman SV Patel. During the daylong event, golfers and caddies got to taste Bidco’s new carbonated soft drink brand. Speaking during the prize-giving ceremony, Bidco Africa director Chris Diaz announced plans to upscale the tournament into an annual event.  Bidco strategy manager Mihir Shah awards Overall Winner (women) Sonia Patel